President Muhammadu Buhari is wishing Vice President ‘Yemi Osinbajo speedy and full recovery, after the latter went through a surgical procedure on Saturday to treat recurrent pain caused by a fracture in his leg. The President, in a statement by his media adviser, Femi Adesina, gave glory to God for a successful surgery, and prayed for “speedy and full recovery.” He also commended the medical team at the Duchess International Hospital, Ikeja, Lagos, for “their competence, and a job well done.” President Buhari assured Osinbajo of the prayers of Nigerians, and that of his family.